metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #36
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: Liaisons Dangereuses... Reloaded #28
metadata.description:
"Liaisons dangereuses" is a creative exploration of implausible relations between figurative art and poetry. Our AI poet learned on the basis of texts about artists and their work. It memorized all subtleties of a language designed to describe visual emotions and artworks. This language is the tool for creating countless poems about artistic concepts, which range from techniques to materials to artists, etc. But the link is two-sided: if the poet is fed by art language, the concepts expressed by poems do, in turn, influence the appearance of the artwork. Color palettes, pattern types and the flow of the graphic composition are indeed determined by the semantics of the poem.
In each minting, the poet will produce either a short poem (a iambic 5-7-5 haiku  or a iambic cinquain according to Adelaide Crapsey style) or a single verse (either an alexandrine, or a iambic pentameter or an anapestic tetrameter). There are 625 artistic concepts that can trigger a poem, and each concept can generate countless different semantically coherent poems. The poet is completely "unchained": contents might be peaceful harmonic assertions as well as embarrassing, politically incorrect claims, but always avoiding inappropriate language.

You can save to file the image by pressing the "s" key.

metadata.name: Provence #337
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.name: Shape Study  #24
metadata.description:
âEveryone has their own shape.â
We meet shapes of all kinds in our life.

Algorithmic randomness generates shapes ever so slightly different yet similar. 
I suppose these are someoneâs collection.

âWhy do they need to have so many similar things?â

Perhaps itâs their versatility in the pleasure they could bring.
Perhaps theyâre meant for different occasions.
Perhaps some are left to search for their very own shapes.

Seeing this, I realized that when people explore themselves or others, it is also a form of shape study.
With whatâs visible and concrete, explore the unseen and abstract.

However, good shapes only come by chance.
Shapes, in truth, cannot be good or bad in and of themselves. Itâs only when two shapes come together that the meaning thereof arises.
I hope you who decide to pick up this work will find the shapes to your liking.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Finestre #278
metadata.description:
"Finestre" means windows or apertures in Italian. This generative art project was inspired by the appreciation of collected memories, windows in time to our past experiences and loved ones. Using basic geometry such as rectangles, squares, circles, ellipses, triangles with random compositions and many possible color palettes, Finestre presents our impression of portals to the Universes of collected memories through abstract still code-based outputs.

Finestre is a collaboration generative art project between generative artists Gonz0x and Schizzo.

Finestre has some fun interactive features which allows collectors to view the work in different configurations. For example, collectors can isolate the deconstructed background layers, isolate the main constructed layer, add Grain and also enter a Free Play mode which allows for the option to draw background and foreground layers, stacking infinitely. You can Save off a render as a .png.

Press "C" for Constructed Mode (Isolate Foreground)
Press "D" for Deconstructed Mode (Isolate Background)
Press "R" to reset to Default = C & D
Press "G" to add grain texture with each press
Press "S" saves render
 
Press "F" to toggle Free Play mode
In Free Play, Press "Q" repeatedly to add Deconstructed layers
In Free Play, Press "W" repeatedly to add Constructed layers
